result.name: Under Bridge Spicy Crab

reviews.text: Food was good but it was too loud as the staff kept talking throughout the whole dinner time. Spicy crab, we chose small size + slightly spicy and it was great for two people with extra vege dish and rice. Plain steamed rice is recommended as the food were quite salty for us so it was great with steamed rice.

The food was disgusting the dishes and utensils were dirty. The service was horrible and they charge a service fee and they also charge for the wipes , tea and the peanuts regardless if you want it or not. The treat people who are not from Hong Kong different . Do not go there if you’re a tourist.

Under bridge is an institution and popular tourist spot for their spicy crab. Like many others have mentioned the service here is not very good and the restaurant is feels a bit grungy and rundown. The crab though is definitely worth trying at least once as it is very good. The other food items I had were tasty but nothing special. 

Food: 4 stars
Environment: 2.5 stars
Service: 3 stars
Overall: 3.5 stars
Recommendations: spicy crab 

We ordered the spicy crab and a small spicy heat level. For me this really wasn’t spicy at all and would go at least medium the next time I come. The crab though is delicious.. They have multiple types of preparations for the crab but you definitely want the typhoon shelter crab. That’s what they are famous for and have a one page display in the menu.

A small crab costs 485 hkd which is pretty expensive. However, the other menu items are not expensive at and are below average price wise especially for a place that is this famous.
You won't go here for surroundings. But you should go for the spicy crab. It's fantastic. Get mildly spicy or above.
Be careful at this place. They are ready to rip you off as soon as they know you are tourist. Make sure your ask for exact price before ordering.

result.name: 橋底辣蟹

reviews.text: 食左10幾年都仍然是咁好食👍保持水準
美味👍😅

이번이 세 번째 방문인데...분명 맛은 있습니다. 하지만 1층 입구쪽 벽에 붙은 테이블에서 식사하는 동안 수많은....정말 말 그대로 수~~많은 바퀴벌레들이 벽과 의자와 커텐위로 사방팔방 이동하는것을 보며 식사하자니 나한테 옮겨 붙을까 불안해서 제대로 즐기지도 못하고 왔네요. 말했더니 의자에 있는 놈 하나 잡아주시고 끝 ㅠㅠ 다음에는 다른 새로운 스파이시 크랩 레스토랑 찾아보려구요.

「橋底辣蟹」由街邊做到成立店舖已經 20 年，每天為蜂湧而至的客人獻上秘製橋底辣蟹。
為了料理出鮮味十足的避風塘菜，老闆每日清晨在魚市場親自揀選生猛海鮮如海蝦、瀨尿蝦、蟶子等。另外也會從外地購入本地沒有的海鮮，如澳洲泥蟹、越南蟹、英國愛爾蘭聖子、馬來西亞瀨尿蝦等。
最值得一試的當然非鎮店招牌菜避風塘炒蟹莫屬！新鮮螃蟹搭配秘製的避風塘佐料大火快炒，辣度有微辣至勁辣五種程度，也有無辣及其它十多種炒法任君選擇，許多饕客更是因遠近馳名的經典辣蟹慕名而來。
走過路過，進去試試看，結果如圖片，蝦好吃可是一隻大約要一千台幣，最後花1496港幣，有點貴。
